            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"key-insights\">Key Insights</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Colombia (53.9) and Brazil (51.6) are the most unequal countries in the dataset, both above 50</li>\n<li>Latin America dominates the top 12 positions, with six countries spanning the 42-46 range</li>\n<li>Northern European countries cluster at the low end: Denmark (29.9), France (31.8), Germany (32.4)</li>\n<li>The global range spans nearly 30 points, underscoring vast differences in income distribution</li>\n</ul></span>"
